<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-159] Splitter does not propagate exceptions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-159</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Splitter in its process method iterates over the body of a message and processes each part synchronously. It does not propogate exceptions thrown by the processor when processing the exchange. This makes it problematic for tryBlock()....handleAll() kind of applications. &lt;/p&gt;
</description>
